        "# 📈 Predicting Crop Yield Based on Rainfall Using Linear Regression#\n",
        "*A simple machine learning project using gradient descent from scratch. My first ML project that I've accomplished using mobile phone*\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "This project is inspired by Week 2 of Andrew Ng's **Supervised Machine Learning** course in the Machine Learning Specialization.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "#Introduction\n",
        "\n",
        "This project demonstrates a basic linear regression model implemented from scratch to predict crop yield (in tons per hectare) based on rainfall (in mm). It includes data normalization, gradient descent training, model visualization, and performance evaluation — all coded without using high-level ML libraries like `sklearn.linear_model`.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Objectives:**\n",
        "- Understand the relationship between rainfall and crop yield.\n",
        "- Implement linear regression with gradient descent manually.\n",
        "- Evaluate model performance using MSE and R².\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "This project helped reinforce the theoretical concepts from Andrew Ng's course through practical application, visualization, and prediction using linear regression.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",

        "import copy\n",

        "\n",
        "# Load the dataset\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('crop_yield.csv')\n",
        "print(df.head())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compute the correlation matrix only for numeric columns\n",
        "corr_matrix = df.select_dtypes(include=['number']).corr()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the correlation matrix\n",
        "print(corr_matrix)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Visualize the correlation matrix\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",

      ]

      "source": [
        "X = df['Rainfall_mm'].values  # Converts to NumPy array\n",
        "y = df['Yield_tons_per_hectare'].values     # Converts to NumPy array\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "##Scatter Plot\n",
        "plt.scatter(X, y, marker='x', c='r')\n",
        "\n",
        "#set title and label\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Rainfall\")\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Feature Scaling: Standardize training and test input data\n",
        "This step ensures the model converges more efficiently during"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "W3djOT55ZRKP"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HmDB12W6q3je"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "split_ratio = 0.8\n",
        "m = len(X)\n",
        "split_index = int(m * split_ratio)\n",
        "\n",
        "indices = np.arange(m)\n",
        "np.random.seed(42)\n",
        "np.random.shuffle(indices)\n",
        "\n",
        "X = X[indices]\n",
        "y = y[indices]\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train = X[:split_index]\n",
        "y_train = y[:split_index]\n",
        "X_test = X[split_index:]\n",
        "y_test = y[split_index:]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "mean_X = np.mean(X_train)\n",
        "std_X = np.std(X_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train = (X_train - mean_X) / std_X\n",
        "X_test = (X_test - mean_X) / std_X\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6oMVGqr22t2e"
      },
      "source": [
        "#COMPUTE COST"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "-tRnFyQk9JQn",
        "outputId": "1ecdebba-397d-4986-eeac-ef1cedef7579"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "<class 'numpy.float64'>\n",
            "Cost at initial w = 2, b = 1: 7.465\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Define the cost function\n",
        "\n",
        "def compute_cost(x, y, w, b):\n",
        "    m = x.shape[0]\n",
        "    f_wb = w * x + b\n",
        "    cost = (1 / (2 * m)) * np.sum((f_wb - y) ** 2)\n",
        "    return cost\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compute cost with initial parameter values\n",
        "initial_w = 2\n",
        "initial_b = 1\n",
        "\n",
        "cost = compute_cost(X_train, y_train, initial_w, initial_b)\n",
        "print(type(cost))\n",
        "print(f'Cost at initial w = {initial_w}, b = {initial_b}: {cost:.3f}')\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zXyi8VkaBZ-U"
      },
      "source": [
        "#📉Compute Gradient for Linear Regression\n",
        "\n",
        "We define a function to compute the gradients of the cost function with respect to the model parameters (weight and bias). These gradients are used to update the parameters during training using gradient descent.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xwAc-BfiBY1H"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def compute_gradient(x, y, w, b):\n",
        "    m = x.shape[0]\n",
        "    f_wb = w * x + b\n",
        "    error = f_wb - y\n",
        "    dj_dw = (1 / m) * np.dot(error, x)\n",
        "    dj_db = (1 / m) * np.sum(error)\n",
        "    return dj_dw, dj_db\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "Kn0vSSK2Cks3",
        "outputId": "8abed9c2-82e4-477d-88fb-91da3b43f1af"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Gradient at initial w, b (zeros): -1.301743288819224 -4.638051072240524\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Compute and display gradient with w initialized to zeroes\n",
        "initial_w = 0\n",
        "initial_b = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "tmp_dj_dw, tmp_dj_db = compute_gradient(X_train, y_train, initial_w, initial_b)\n",
        "print('Gradient at initial w, b (zeros):', tmp_dj_dw, tmp_dj_db)\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },

        "# Compute and display cost and gradient with non-zero w\n",
        "test_w = 0.2\n",
        "test_b = 0.2\n",
        "tmp_dj_dw, tmp_dj_db = compute_gradient(X_train, y_train, test_w, test_b)\n",

      ]

    {

      "metadata": {
        "id": "jVFGNyCuDI8X"
      },
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "#🧠 Train the Model Using Gradient Descent#\n",
        "\n",
        "We set the initial values of the model parameters and run gradient descent using the specified learning rate and number of iterations. The output is the optimized weight and bias for our linear regression model.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def gradient_descent(x, y, w_in, b_in, cost_function, gradient_function, alpha, num_iters):\n",
        "    J_history = []\n",
        "    w_history = []\n",
        "    w = copy.deepcopy(w_in)\n",
        "    b = b_in\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(num_iters):\n",
        "        dj_dw, dj_db = gradient_function(x, y, w, b)\n",
        "        w -= alpha * dj_dw\n",
        "        b -= alpha * dj_db\n",
        "\n",
        "        if i < 100000:\n",
        "            cost = cost_function(x, y, w, b)\n",
        "            J_history.append(cost)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if i % math.ceil(num_iters / 10) == 0:\n",
        "            w_history.append(w)\n",
        "            print(f\"Iteration {i:4}: Cost {J_history[-1]:8.2f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return w, b, J_history, w_history\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "231aAMUL-MLI"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
